==English==
===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /θ/

===Etymology 1===
Representing Old English [[-þ]].

====Suffix====
'''-th'''
# forming nouns from verbs of action
#:''[[growth]]'', ''[[spilth]]'', ''[[death]]''
# forming nouns from adjectives
#:''[[filth]]'', ''[[strength]]''

===Etymology 2===
Representing Old English ''-þa, -þe, -oþa, -oþe'', derived from an Indo-European superlative suffix.

====Suffix====
'''-th'''
# Used to form the [[ordinal]] [[numeral]] when the final term of the spelled number is not "first", "second", or "third".
#: ''The 4th of July''

====See also====
*[[-nd]]
*[[-rd]]
*[[-st]]

[[Category:English suffixes|rd]]

===Etymology 3===
Representing Old English ''-eþ, -aþ, -þ''.

====Suffix====
'''-th'''
# a variant of [[-eth]], used to form the [[archaic]] [[third person singular]] of verbs
#:''come-->cometh''

